text:
Mar 21, 2017 at 10:51a ET 0Shares 
There are 39 drivers on the Monster Energy Cup Series entry list as NASCAR will make its final stop out West with Sunday’s race at Auto Club Speedway. 
No teams, will be forced to pack up and go home following Friday’s qualifying session. Check out all the drivers that will hit the 2-mile Fontana, California track for the Auto Club 400. Jamie McMurray 
McMurray has shown speed all season. He’ll look to improve on his 10 th -place finish in last year’s race at Auto Club. Brad Keselowski 
Keselowski earned his only victory at the California track in 2014. Doug Pensinger Austin Dillon 
In three races at Auto Club in the No. 3 Richard Childress Racing Chevy, Dillon has finishes of 11 th , 16 th and 24 th respectively. Kevin Harvick 
Harvick has started second and finished second in the past two races at Auto Club. He also has a win there in 2011. Kasey Kahne 
Kahne has shown a ton of improvement so far this season. His best finish at Auto Club in the No. 5 Hendrick Motorsports Chevy came in 2013, finishing 9 th . Brett Moist Trevor Bayne 
In three Cup races at Auto Club, Bayne only has a highest finish of 20 th . He hasn’t finish worse than 19 th so far this season, so we’ll see if he can continue the momentum by scoring his a career-best finish at the 2-mile oval. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Russell LaBounty Danica Patrick 
Patrick had a rough go of it in 2016 at Auto Club after getting taken out by Kasey Kahne. After three finishes outside the top 20 in the first four races of the season, she’s could use a solid result. Nigel Kinrade/LAT Photo USA 
Hamlin started third and finished there in this race last season. Ty Dillon 
Sunday’s race will be the rookie’s first in a Cup car at Auto Club. Clint Bowyer 
Bowyer’s highest finish at Auto Club a third-place finish back in 2006. So far in 2017, he has third straight top-15 finishes. Reed Sorenson 
Sorenson will be back in the No. 15 for Premium Motorsports. Ricky Stenhouse Jr. 
Stenhouse scored a fourth-place finish in last Sunday’s race at Phoenix Kyle Busch 
The 2015 Cup champion has three wins at Auto Club, which includes his first career victory in 2005. © Russell LaBounty/LAT Photo USA Russell LaBounty Daniel Suarez 
Suarez is another rookie who’ll be making his first Cup start at the 2-mile track. , LAT Images www.latimages.co.uk Nigel Kinrade Matt Kenseth 
All three of Kenseth’s wins at Auto Club came during his Roush Fenway Racing days. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Russell LaBounty Ryan Blaney 
Blaney is hoping Sunday’s race is better than last year where a crash resulted in a 35 th -place finish. Joey Logano 
Logano has never won at Auto Club. His best finish of 3 rd came in 2013. © Russell LaBounty/LAT Photo USA Russell LaBounty Gray Gaulding 
The 18-year-old will make his first start in Fontana on Sunday. © Matthew T. Thacker/LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Matthew T. Thacker Chase Elliott 
Elliott is on the cusp of his first career Cup win. He had a strong showing at Auto Club last year, finishing sixth , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Russell LaBounty Paul Menard 
This track has been good for Menard the past four seasons, with finishes of eighth, ninth, fourth and 15 th respectively. Ryan Newman 
It’s all about collecting max points now for Newman as he upset victory at Phoenix landed him in the playoffs early. Matt DiBenedetto 
After a ninth-place finish in the Daytona 500, DiBenedetto has three straight finishes outside the top 25. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk John K Harrelson Jeffrey Earnhardt 
Earnhardt finished 34 th in the No. 32 GO Fas Racing Ford at Auto Club last year. Landon Cassill 
Cassill earned his career-best finish at Auto Club last season, finishing 16 th . Chris Buescher 
It’s been a rough start to the season for Buescher with a new team. His best finish is 23 rd in Las Vegas. David Ragan 
Ragan’s best finish at Auto Club came in 2009 where he finished seventh in a Roush Fenway Racing Ford. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Michael L. Levitt Kurt Busch 
You’d have to look all the way back to the 2003 season for Busch’s one win at Auto Club. Kyle Larson 
Larson’s run of five consecutive runner-up finishes has been remarkable. Ironically, his best finish at Auto Club came in 2014, where he finished second. Aric Almirola 
Almirola’s best finish at Auto Club came in 2015 where he finished 11 th . AJ Allmendinger 
The ‘Dinger finished eighth in this race last year. A result like that again on Sunday could get his season back on track. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Russell LaBounty Jimmie Johnson 
Auto Club is home to Johnson’s first career win in 2002, the first of six victories to date at the 2-mile track. The El Cajon, California boy is also the defending race winner. Getty Images Robert Laberge Timmy Hill 
Hill has one start in the Monster Energy Series at Auto Club, finishing 39 th in 2013. Derrike Cope 
The 1990 Daytona 500 winner will pilot the No. 55 this weekend. Cole Whitt 
Whitt finished 18 th in his first Cup race at Auto Club in 2014. Erik Jones 
The rookie is looking to build on an impressive eighth-place finish last Sunday at Phoenix. © Matthew T. Thacker/LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Matthew T. Thacker Martin Truex Jr. 
Truex will be searching for his first Auto Club victory and his second of the season on Sunday. Corey LaJoie 
LaJoie's first season in the No. 83 BK Racing Toyota hasn't been a walk in the park with two DNFs. © Matthew T. Thacker/LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Matthew T. Thacker Dale Earnhardt Jr. 
Earnhardt's best finish is second at Auto Club in 2013. He'll be back in the No. 88 "FlashPoint" paint scheme this weekend. © Matthew T. Thacker/LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Matthew T. Thacker Michael McDowell
